data.title: SAVED21cm: Global 21cm signal extraction pipeline
data.name: SAVED21cm
data.description: A toolbox for extracting the 21cm signal from the simulated mock observation for REACH.

evidence: "SAVED21cm: A global 21cm signal extraction pipeline" indicates it is an end-user pipeline application for data analysis, not a reusable library.

"This is a global 21cm signal extraction pipeline, specifically build for the REACH experiment, but in principle can be utilized for any global 21cm experiment" shows it directly performs scientific signal extraction central to research results.
The README only presents the code and a figure from `./tests/FigsOutput/...` with no mention of package managers, binaries, or hosted services, implying distribution via the source repository.
